ASAN crash only reproduces with `--clean` and `-c`, not when exchanging either of those with e.g. `-u NONE` and `--cmd`. I guess that further suggests that this is just a startup issue; maybe we can add some logic there instead. I.e. this works:

```diff
diff --git a/src/nvim/main.c b/src/nvim/main.c
index 30b6b6e86b..111edf6709 100644
--- a/src/nvim/main.c
+++ b/src/nvim/main.c
@@ -613,6 +613,11 @@ int main(int argc, char **argv)
     TIME_MSG("UIEnter autocommands");
   }

+  // Startup commands may have invalidated the cached 'numberwidth' value #28984.
+  FOR_ALL_WINDOWS_IN_TAB(wp, curtab) {
+    wp->w_nrwidth_line_count = 0;
+  }
+
 #ifdef MSWIN
   if (use_remote_ui) {
     os_icon_init();
```

